<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak " data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<p>Department for International Trade (<abbr title="Department for International Trade">DIT</abbr>) promotes British trade across the world and ensures the UK takes advantage of the huge opportunities open to us. This secures and improves the economic well-being and stability of the UK, and helps create tens of thousands of jobs every year.</p>

<p>Read <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-international-trade/about">more about what we do</a> and the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-international-trade/about/about-our-services">services we provide</a>.</p>

<h2 id="current-jobs">Current jobs</h2>

<p>We advertise all our UK jobs on the <a rel="external" href="https://www.civilservicejobs.service.gov.uk/csr/index.cgi">Civil Service jobs site</a>.</p>

<p>Local overseas vacancies are advertised on <a rel="external" href="https://fco.tal.net/vx/lang-en-GB/mobile-0/appcentre-ext/brand-2/xf-7810a1ba3247/candidate/jobboard/vacancy/1/adv/">Foreign and Commonwealth Office (<abbr title="Foreign and Commonwealth Office">FCO</abbr>) Local Posts</a>. Applicants for local roles are based in that country and need to be able to work in the main local language.</p>

<p>Find out about working for the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/civil-service/about/recruitment">Civil Service</a>.</p>

<h2 id="our-staff">Our staff</h2>

<p>We employ staff in London, across the UK and around the world. Our teams overseas are made up of UK-based British civil servants and colleagues who are employed locally by a British Diplomatic mission overseas.</p>

<h2 id="develop-your-career-in-dit">Develop your career in <abbr title="Department for International Trade">DIT</abbr>
</h2>

<p>We offer a wide variety of career opportunities – from developing and negotiating free trade agreements to promoting export and investment opportunities. We value professional expertise that includes:</p>

<ul>
  <li>policy making and delivery</li>
  <li>contract management</li>
  <li>finance</li>
  <li>marketing and communications</li>
  <li>human resources (HR)</li>
  <li>digital</li>
  <li>project management</li>
  <li>event delivery</li>
</ul>

<p>We are an <a rel="external" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2010/15/contents">equal opportunities</a> employer.</p>

<h2 id="benefits-of-working-for-dit">Benefits of working for <abbr title="Department for International Trade">DIT</abbr>
</h2>

<p><abbr title="Department for International Trade">DIT</abbr> is a rewarding place to work, offering:</p>

<ul>
  <li>job satisfaction: making a positive contribution to the UK’s economy</li>
  <li>flexible working</li>
  <li>family friendly policies including maternity, adoption or shared parental leave, available with up to 26 weeks full pay, followed by 13 weeks statutory pay and a further 13 weeks unpaid</li>
  <li>2 weeks full pay available for paternity leave</li>
  <li>unique and exciting roles within government</li>
  <li>learning and development opportunities</li>
  <li>an equal and diverse workplace</li>
  <li>opportunities to travel and work overseas</li>
  <li>competitive salaries and benefits packages</li>
</ul>

</div>
